  "instructions": [
    "Heat the vegetable oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the minced garlic, chopped ginger, and diced onion; sauté until the onion turns translucent, about 3 minutes.",
    "Add the sliced bamboo shoots and stir for 2 minutes, letting them absorb the aromatics.",
    "Pour in the coconut broth and bring to a gentle boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes, allowing the bamboo shoots to become tender.",
    "Stir in the coconut milk and fish sauce, then add lime juice, sugar, salt, and chili flakes if using.",
    "Simmer the soup for an additional 10 minutes, letting the flavors meld and the soup thicken slightly.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning, adding more salt or lime if needed.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with fresh cilantro and basil leaves.",
    "Optionally, accompany with steamed rice or gluten-free flatbread for a complete meal."
  ],
